[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'AI has no taste, and it\'s your fault. The reason your visual outputs are so mediocre is because your prompts are so mediocre. You aren\'t using the type of terminology, language, and nomenclature that an actual designer would be using. But luckily for us, I found a solution.'

[00:13] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'It\'s called impeccable, and it\'s an open-source GitHub repo that for all intents and purposes is a single skill that we can import into Claude Code that fixes this exact problem. It provides'

[00:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Claude Code a design language that teaches it what good design actually looks like, while also telling it what sort of bad designs to avoid. And today, I\'m not only going to show you how this'

[00:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'skill works, we are going to use it to build a brand new website and to edit one of my websites that already exists. So by the end of this video, you are going to have no excuse when it comes to creating mediocre front-end designs. So Impeccable is an open-source GitHub repo'

[00:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that gives us a single skill that allows us to create front-end designs that don\'t suck. Now, it\'s a single skill, but that\'s underplaying it a little bit because this single skill includes 23'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'different commands. It has seven domain-specific reference files. It tells us, you know, what sort of anti-patterns to avoid, and it even allows us to edit things inside of our browser. So'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'this is actually a very robust tool. This isn\'t just the front-end design skill that goes on for a few paragraphs about what Claude Code should be doing. But that complexity can be a little overwhelming because there is literally'

[01:27] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '23 different commands that do a number of different things as it relates to your design. Now, it breaks them all down here inside of the repo, but the truth is you\'re never going to remember all these. But there\'s two things that'

[01:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'help out here. One, obviously Claude Code\'s going to do a pretty good job of figuring out which one you should use. But secondly, they have an entire website that also shows us what it is each of these 23 skills do. So the'

[01:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'GitHub links to the website, which is impeccable.style. And the cool thing is for every single applicable skill, we can see what something looks like before, which is plain cloud code, and what it looks like after using that'

[02:04] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'specific impeccable command. So, pretty neat. Now, impeccable really has seven pillars of design, typography, color, spatial design, responsiveness, interactions, and motion, and UX writing. So, it isn\'t just going for,'

[02:16] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you know, like colors and things like that. It\'s pretty comprehensive. And right here, we can scroll through all of these different commands. And like I said, see what they look like using the skill and not using the skill.'

